            In front of this church there are 29 steps to enter this church. The interior of this church is decorated with beautiful decorations, and the pulpit is supported by thirteen pillars that symbolize Jesus Christ and His disciples. The unique thing is that the pillar for Judas Iscariot is black to signify his betrayal to Jesus, while the pillar for Thomas is gray, because he was a doubtful disciple when Jesus appeared to His disciples.
