            According to tradition, this place is believed to be the place where Pharaoh's daughter found and raised baby Moses from the water. Now this place stands a synagogue, which is a place of worship for the Jewish people. Previously the building located behind the Hanging Church was a church, which was later sold to the Jews in 882, to pay taxes to the Muslim rulers of the time. A Jew named Abraham Ben Ezra came from Jerusalem during the reign of Ahmed Ibn Tulun who bought it for 20,000 dinars.
